caption: Table 1: Performance comparison of proprietary, open-source, and supervised fine-tuned models across three medical benchmarks. The metrics include accuracy (Acc.) and average output token length (Avg. Token). Mean Acc. represents the weighted average across the three datasets. The best score excluding closed-source APIs was bolded, and the second-best score was underlined.
description: This table presents a comprehensive comparison of various LLMs' performance on three medical benchmarks (JAMA Clinical Challenge, Medbullets, and MedQA).  It compares proprietary models (GPT-4, o1-mini, o1-preview), open-source models (Qwen2.5, InternLM, LLaMa), and those fine-tuned using two different methods: supervised fine-tuning with vanilla Chain-of-Thought (CoT) and the proposed journey learning approach (LongStep and LongMonolog).  The metrics shown are accuracy and average output token length. The weighted average accuracy across all three datasets is also provided.  The best-performing open-source model for each benchmark is highlighted.
